⊢ eval-one
  given §program
  yield §program', stepped-cell

  ∴ Read «§program». Find all cells whose given inputs
    are fully bound (all ≡ values present). Pick ONE
    such cell. Execute it (fill in its yield ≡ values).
    Return the updated program with that one cell executed.
    Report which cell was stepped.

  ⊨ §program' differs from «§program» in exactly one cell
  ⊨ stepped-cell names the cell that was executed
  ⊨ the stepped cell's yields now have ≡ bindings
  ⊨ all other cells in §program' are unchanged

⊢ is-done
  given §program
  yield done

  ∴ Check whether all cells in «§program» have their
    yields fully bound. If so, the program is complete.

  ⊨ done is a boolean

⊢ hash
  given §program
  yield digest

  ∴ Compute a content hash of «§program».

  ⊨ digest is a string
  ⊨ same §program always produces same digest

⊢∘ run(§target-program)
  through eval-one, hash
  until is-done(eval-one→§program')
  max 100

  ⊨ final §program' has all yields bound
  ⊨ each step produces a unique hash (no cycles)
